@bradh352 As I understand it, you enounter a crash that reveals design issues of kernel configuration of ports/lags - port and lag kernel configuration are inherently dependent but portmgrd and teammgrd are running completelly unaware of each other. The ```mtu``` field of the port becomes meaningless when port is enslaved as it inherits lag mtu, but is used later in teammgrd when removing a lag member to restore port mtu to its original value.
Given solution to check lag member configuration is still prone to data races post boot.
On the other hand, you seem to be more concerned about the crash behaviour, how about not crash when ```ip``` command fails, instead, report an error in syslog? A correct mtu value will be restored by teammgrd if user removes lag member configuration.

